AND HIGH DOSE REGN2810 (CEMIPLIMAB; ANTI-PD-1 ANTIBODY) AND IPILIMUMAB (ANTI-CTLA-4

datastring.dstemplatestring:
Initial received date: 29MAR2019

Follow-up received date(s): 29Mar19, 02,04,05, 22Apr19, 06-07,08,10,15,16-17,20,27 May19, 26Jun19, 12Jul19, 19Aug19,
13,17Sep19, 08,25,310ct19,21Nov19,6Aug20,16Sep20, 040ct20, O6Oct20, 210ct20, O3Nov20 and 04Nov20, 12Nov20

STROKE (initially reported as UNCONSCIOVSNESS) [Cerebrovascular accident]: Death; Onset date: 28MAR19, Severity: Grade 5;
Outcome: Fatal on 28MAR19

THROMBOEMBOLIC COMPLICATION (BRAINSTEM)[Embolism] (previously THROMBOEMBOLIC COMPLICATION [Embolism]):
Hospitalization; Onset date: 27MAR19, Severity: Grade 4; Outcome: Not Recovered / Not Resolved

A 77 years-old, male, Caucasian patient, with Non-small cell lung cancer was enrolled in study R2810-ONC-1763. The patient
experienced above-referenced SAEs on 27MAR1Q, after receiving study drug. The patient died on 28Mar19. The cause of death was
reported as unconsciousness and Bradypnoe. It was unknown if an autopsy was performed.

The patient received first dose of REGN2810 (Cemiplimab) 1050mg intravenous (IV) every 3 weeks (Q3W) on 14Feb2019. The most
recent dose of REGN2810 (Cemiplimab), prior to onset of event was administered on 07Mar19, and the patient received a total of 2
doses prior to the onset of the event. Study drug was temporarily withdrawn because the patient died.

The patient received first dose of Ipilimumab 50mg IV,Q6W for up to 4 doses, on an unknown date. The most recent dose of
Ipilimumab, prior to onset of event was administered on an unknown date, and the patient received a total of unknown doses prior to
the onset of the event. Action taken was reported as not-applicable.

On 22Mar19, the patient experienced oedema of upper body (face, neck, larynx and upper limbs) and experienced cyanosis on
25Mar19. On 27Mar19, both events became serious. The event of oedema of upper body (face, neck, larynx and upper limbs) was
considered to be related the immune-mediated mechanism of action of REGN2810 (Cemiplimab). Initial severity was reported as
Grade 2 and the most extreme severity was Grade 5 (pending clarification). The event became Grade 3 or higher on 28Mar19. The
event of cyanosis was reported as immune related event with etiology of edema (pending clarification). The outcome for the events
was not recovered/not resolved. Additional treatment started on 27Mar19 included Warfin for hypertension and opacorden for
persistent atrial fibrillation. On 28Mar19, the patient experienced unconsciousness, bradypnoe and hemiparesis. Initial severity and
the most extreme severity was reported as Grade 5 for both the events of unconsciousness and bradypnoe. The events became
Grade 3 or higher on 28Mar19. Hemiparesis initial severity and the most extreme severity was reported as Grade 2. On 28Mar-19,
the events of unconsciousness and bradypnoe resulted in fatal outcome. The event of hemiparesis was not recovered/not resolved.
Treatment for the events was noted as Tulip; Acetylsalicylic acid and Areplex on 16Oct18 (pending clarification). The sub investigator
